Encryption Software: Encrypts data to prevent unauthorized access.
Data Loss Prevention (DLP) Solutions: Monitors and prevents sensitive data from leaving the organization.
Firewall Systems: Protects networks by controlling incoming and outgoing network traffic.
Intrusion Detection Systems (IDS): Monitors network traffic for suspicious activities and alerts on potential security breaches.
Intrusion Prevention Systems (IPS): Detects and blocks malicious activities to prevent network attacks.
Secure Web Gateways: Filters web traffic to prevent access to malicious or inappropriate websites.
Identity and Access Management (IAM) Solutions: Manages user identities and controls access to data and systems.
Security Information and Event Management (SIEM) Systems: Collects and analyzes security logs and events to detect threats.
Data Masking and Anonymization Tools: Protects sensitive data by disguising or anonymizing it.
Tokenization Solutions: Replaces sensitive data with non-sensitive tokens to protect it during transmission and storage.
Data Classification Tools: Identifies and classifies sensitive data to enforce proper security controls.
Database Activity Monitoring (DAM) Solutions: Monitors database activity for suspicious or unauthorized access.
Endpoint Protection Platforms (EPP): Protects endpoints such as laptops, desktops, and mobile devices from malware and unauthorized access.
Secure File Transfer Protocols (SFTP): Ensures secure file transfer over a network.
Secure Email Gateways: Filters and protects email communication from spam, phishing, and malware.
Data Encryption Key Management Systems: Manages encryption keys used to encrypt and decrypt data.
Two-Factor Authentication (2FA) Solutions: Adds an extra layer of security by requiring two forms of authentication for accessing systems and data.
Security Incident and Event Management (SIEM) Platforms: Collects and analyzes security logs and events from various sources to identify and respond to threats.
Virtual Private Networks (VPNs): Creates a secure and encrypted connection between remote users and the corporate network.
Web Application Firewalls (WAF): Protects web applications from attacks and vulnerabilities.
Mobile Device Management (MDM) Solutions: Manages and secures mobile devices used within an organization.
Data Backup and Recovery Solutions: Regularly backs up data and provides mechanisms for recovery in case of data loss or system failure.
Secure Code Analysis Tools: Scans and identifies security vulnerabilities in application code.
Data Governance Tools: Helps organizations manage and enforce data privacy and security policies.
Security Awareness Training Platforms: Provides training and education to employees on cybersecurity best practices and awareness.